# Meta-Theory Dispatch (Cursor)

This repository treats ordinary durable natural-language work as the entry
surface for Meta_Kim governance. In Cursor, the stable entry is this rule plus
the project hooks in `.cursor/hooks.json`; do not wait for a Claude/Codex slash
command file to appear.

## Mandatory Entry Cases

Use the governed Meta_Kim route when the prompt contains any of these shapes:

- explicit `meta-theory`, `/meta-theory`, `元理论`, `critical and fetch thinking and review`
- project / repo / codebase understanding, for example "what is this project",
  "这个项目干啥", "这个项目怎么玩", "analyze this repo"
- architecture, runtime, hook, MCP, capability, agent, skill, or tool routing
- commercialization, market, competitor, pricing, customer, investor, growth,
  strategy, roadmap, or current external-platform claims
- any durable execution request that will edit, test, publish, install, sync,
  release, or make a public-ready claim

## Required Route

When one of the entry cases matches, Cursor must run or faithfully follow the
machine entry:

```sh
npm run meta:theory:run -- "<user request>"
```

If the command cannot run because dependencies, permissions, shell access, or
runtime support are missing, stop before shallow analysis and record a blocker:
`blocked_to_fetch` with the exact missing capability. Do not answer from a
quick summary as if Fetch happened.

## Deep Fetch Minimum

Project-understanding and strategy tasks must inspect or explicitly account for
all of these source classes before Thinking:

- `README.md` / `README.zh-CN.md`
- `AGENTS.md` and runtime-maintainer instructions
- `package.json` scripts and executable commands
- `canonical/agents/`, `canonical/skills/`, `canonical/runtime-assets/`
- `config/contracts/`, `config/capability-index/`, runtime and OS matrices
- `.cursor/`, `.claude/`, `.codex/`, and `openclaw/` runtime projections
- MCP configs, heartbeat files, hooks, and dependency-project registry
- Graphify: `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` or `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` when present
- prior run/evolution records when the task asks about history or learning

For market, competitor, pricing, provider, version, platform, or current-world
claims, Fetch must first prove an available retrieval path such as web search,
URL fetch, browser, MCP provider, docs lookup, or a recorded local-only
justification. If no retrieval path is available, return `blocked_to_fetch`
instead of guessing.

## Output Discipline

The user-facing response can stay human and compact, but the run must leave
auditable evidence: `fetchRecord.capabilitySearchPerformed = true`,
`capabilityInventory`, `dispatchBoard`, `workerTaskPackets`, Review,
Meta-Review, Verification, and Evolution writeback or `none-with-reason`.

Cursor-specific rule: do not paste Claude Code hook payloads or Codex TOML into
Cursor rules. Cursor uses `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`, `.cursor/hooks.json`,
`.cursor/hooks/`, `.cursor/agents/*.md`, and `.cursor/mcp.json`.
